<dl id="n58040c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n58" href="#n58040c">N58 (VI.B.30)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n58all.htm#n58040c"> 40(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> glove for / peace / reverse of / shield <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n58040c"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[THE PURSUIT OF DIARMUID AND GRAINNE]</font> <font color="green">[The steward&apos;s prophecy is fulfilled. Diarmuid is goared by the pig and dies, Finn having refused to revive him by means of his magic. Angus learns of the death of his foster-son and proceeds to Benn Gulban, arriving there]</font> at the same time with the people of Grainne; and when Grainne&apos;s household recognised Angus <mark>they held out the rough side of their shields in token of peace</mark> <small> Tom Peete Cross and Clark Harris Slover, <a name="AIT2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AIT2"><cite title="source">Ancient Irish Tales</cite></a> ([Nov. 1936]) 416</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
